The simulated SM contributions in each of the channels considered are separated into prompt-lepton and fake-lepton contributions, depending on the source of the reconstructed leptons at generator level. The processes that contain only reconstructed charged leptons originating from prompt leptonic decays of W and Z bosons are classified as a prompt-lepton contribution, while processes with at least one of the reconstructed leptons being a misidentified hadron or photon, or a lepton from hadron decays constitute the fake-lepton contribution. The simulated events are not used to evaluate the background originating from charge-misidentified leptons for the 2ℓss\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
